repository.corpname: Beinecke Rare Book and Manuscript Library

did.abstract: Contains chiefly British (as well as other European and American) historical and literary manuscripts and autographs, including items by James Boswell, Jr., Hall Caine, Thomas Frognall Dibdin, John Masefield, Mary Russell Mitford, Richard Brinsley Sheridan, Algernon Charles Swinburne, Anthony Trollope, and John Wilkes.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: The Chauncey Brewster Tinker Manuscript Collection is the physical property of the Beinecke Rare Book and Manuscript Library, Yale University. Literary rights, including copyright, belong to the authors or their legal heirs and assigns. For further information, consult the appropriate curator.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Chauncey Brewster Tinker Manuscript Collection. General Collection, Beinecke Rare Book and Manuscript Library, Yale University.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The materials are open for research.
Box 21: Restricted fragile material. Reference surrogates have been substituted in the main files. For further information consult the appropriate curator.

relatedmaterial.head: Associated Materials
relatedmaterial.p: Chauncey Brewster Tinker Papers (GEN MSS 354) and various printed books donated to the Library by Tinker are cataloged separately.

bioghist.head: BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE
bioghist.p: Chauncey Brewster Tinker (1876-1963), Yale Class of 1899, was a member of the Department of English at Yale University, the author of several books about James Boswell, and Keeper of Rare Books in the Rare Book Room at Sterling Memorial Library at Yale. Tinker inspired Frank Altschul to start what later became the Yale Library Associates. Many of the literary and historical manuscripts that Tinker acquired personally he gave to the Yale Library.

For additional information, see the numerous references to Chauncey Brewster Tinker in the index to The Yale University Library Gazette , and the memorial written at the time of his death and printed in the Gazette , Vol. 38, Number 1 (July 1963).

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This finding aid is a partial regrouping of historical and literary manuscripts from Chauncey Brewster Tinker's personal collection. It does not account for all of the manuscripts given by Tinker to the library. Other groups of Tinker manuscripts (e.g., Arnold, Byron, and Carlyle) remain in previously cataloged collections. Approximately one-third of the manuscripts listed here are described in The Tinker Library: A Bibliographical Catalogue of the Books and Manuscripts Collected by Chauncey Brewster Tinker , compiled by Robert F. Metzdorf (New Haven: Yale University Press, 1959), and are identified here by their Tinker numbers. Other manuscripts in this Collection are not listed in the printed guide and do not have Tinker numbers.

The Collection is arranged alphabetically by author and contains chiefly British, as well as other European and American historical and literary manuscripts and autographs. Each entry in this list was transcribed from the library's card catalog; in some cases, information from entries in the printed guide has been incorporated. Individuals represented in the files include: Matthew Arnold, James Boswell, Jr., Hall Caine, Thomas Frognall Dibdin, John Masefield, Mary Russell Mitford, Alexander Pope, Richard Brinsley Sheridan, Algernon Charles Swinburne, Anthony Trollope, John Wilkes, and William Wordsworth. Many individuals are represented by fewer than five manuscripts, and in many cases by only one. Many of the letters are addressed to William Hepworth Dixon. Oversize material has been housed separately, and cross references have been made. Between 1998 and 2005 additional material was restored to the Tinker Manuscript Collection.
